    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters April 25th with a clear focal point in **Corbin Carroll**, who commands today\u2019s slate with an elite 85.94 score. Facing M\u00e1rquez (5.26 xERA), **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a massive 19% SP skill boost and a slow delivery factor that screams upside for our scarcest category: stolen bases. Joining him in the \"Strong\" tier is **Seiya Suzuki** (69.55), who draws a favorable matchup against Sasaki (5.52 xERA) with wind conditions providing an extra 5% lift. **Brice Turang** (65.39) remains a locked-in core play, leveraging his elite lead-off spot against Keller to keep our SB volume high, despite a slight drag from the catcher\u2019s arm. Meanwhile, **Trevor Story** (63.84) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (63.16) round out our aggressive core, with **Trevor Story** specifically primed by a significant 16% park factor enhancement that pushes him well above his raw projection.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision today involved **Alex Freeland**, who posted a respectable 49.73 score but narrowly missed the cut due to the aggressive lineup density surrounding our middle infielders. While his switch-hitting profile and favorable wind conditions were tempting, the decision to favor the higher floor of **Max Muncy** (52.59) and the specific platoon advantages of our starters ultimately won out. We are also monitoring **Vinnie Pasquantino** (53.20) closely; while he holds a strong spot in the 3-hole, he faces the toughest matchup of the day against Urena (2.35 xERA), forcing a heavy 19% downgrade to his SP skill score. Managers should be aware that **Mickey Moniak** is effectively sidelined by a rainout, ensuring he remains on the bench to protect our limited game caps while we wait for more favorable weather windows for his profile.",
